      "version": "0.0.1",
      "release_notes": "## VoiceInput 0.0.1\n\nThis is the first public starting release of VoiceInput.\n\nVoiceInput is a cross-platform project for sending text from an Android phone to a desktop machine and inserting it directly into the current input target.\n\n### Included in this release\n- Android client\n- Desktop client for multiple operating systems\n- Initial public version baseline\n\n### Asset guide\n\n#### Android\n- `voiceinput-android-v0.0.1.apk`  \n  Android installation package.\n\n#### Windows\n- `voiceinput-desktop-windows-x64-v0.0.1.msi`  \n  Standard Windows installer package.\n- `voiceinput-desktop-windows-x64-v0.0.1-setup.exe`  \n  Windows setup executable.\n\n#### macOS\n- `voiceinput-desktop-macos-x64-v0.0.1.dmg`  \n  Desktop package for Intel Macs.\n- `voiceinput-desktop-macos-arm64-v0.0.1.dmg`  \n  Desktop package for Apple Silicon Macs.\n\n#### Linux\n- `voiceinput-desktop-linux-x64-v0.0.1.deb`  \n  Debian/Ubuntu package.\n- `voiceinput-desktop-linux-x64-v0.0.1.AppImage`  \n  Portable Linux package.\n\n### Notes\n- `0.0.1` is the first public starting point of the project.\n- Future releases will evolve from this baseline.",
